               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t16810706a-4-defend14" type="defendantName">
                  Elisabeth 
                  Maidstone, alias <rs id="t16810706a-4-alias-1" type="alias">
                        <join result="nameAlias" targOrder="Y"
                              targets="t16810706a-4-defend14 t16810706a-4-alias-1"/>Moor</rs>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-defend14" type="surname" value="Maidstone"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-defend14" type="given" value="Elisabeth"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-defend14" type="gender" value="female"/>
                  </persName>
            , was Tryed for <rs id="t16810706a-4-off13" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-off13" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-off13" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"/>
               stealing 2 Handcarcheifs, a pair of Sleeves, Ruffles, Coifs, and other Linnen, to the value of ten shillings
            </rs>, from 
               
                  <persName id="t16810706a-4-victim16" type="victimName">
                     Elisabeth 
                     Manly
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-4-victim16" type="surname" value="Manly"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-victim16" type="given" value="Elisabeth"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-victim16" type="gender" value="female"/>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-4-off13 t16810706a-4-victim16"/>
                  </persName>
               
             in <placeName id="t16810706a-4-crimeloc14">Corn-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-4-crimeloc14" type="placeName" value="Corn-hill"/>
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-4-crimeloc14" type="type" value="crimeLocation"/>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y"
                        targets="t16810706a-4-off13 t16810706a-4-crimeloc14"/>, the things were proved to be taken upon her, and after a short denyal, she Confessed the Robery, and was brought in <rs id="t16810706a-4-verdict15" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-4-verdict15" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"/>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
   
   
            <div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16810706a-5">
               <interp inst="t16810706a-5" type="collection" value="BAILEY"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-5" type="year" value="1681"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-5" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16810706A"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-5" type="date" value="16810706"/>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16810706a-5-off16-c13" targOrder="Y"
                     targets="t16810706a-5-defend18 t16810706a-5-off16 t16810706a-5-verdict19"/>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16810706a-5-off16-c14" targOrder="Y"
                     targets="t16810706a-5-defend20 t16810706a-5-off16 t16810706a-5-verdict19"/>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16810706a-5-defend18" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Gibson
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend18" type="surname" value="Gibson"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend18" type="given" value="Thomas"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend18" type="gender" value="male"/>
                  </persName>
               
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t16810706a-5-defend20" type="defendantName">
                     Robert 
                     Hawkson
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend20" type="surname" value="Hawkson"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend20" type="given" value="Robert"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-defend20" type="gender" value="male"/>
                  </persName>
               
            , were Tryed for <rs id="t16810706a-5-off16" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-off16" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-off16" type="offenceSubcategory" value="robbery"/>
               setting upon, and Robing 
                     
                        <persName id="t16810706a-5-victim22" type="victimName">
                           Edward 
                           Bets
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-5-victim22" type="surname" value="Bets"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-5-victim22" type="given" value="Edward"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-5-victim22" type="gender" value="male"/>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y"
                              targets="t16810706a-5-off16 t16810706a-5-victim22"/>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , <rs id="t16810706a-5-viclabel17" type="occupation">Servant</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-5-victim22 t16810706a-5-viclabel17"/> to 
                     <persName id="t16810706a-5-person23">
                        Richard 
                        Cradeck
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-person23" type="surname" value="Cradeck"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-5-person23" type="given" value="Richard"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-5-person23" type="gender" value="male"/>
                     </persName>
                   Esq; near <placeName id="t16810706a-5-crimeloc18">Newington</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-crimeloc18" type="placeName" value="Newington"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-crimeloc18" type="type" value="crimeLocation"/>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-5-off16 t16810706a-5-crimeloc18"/>, taking from him, 2 Gowns, 2 peices of Silk. Mony and other things to the value of 20 l.
            </rs> and after having beat and bound him, they made for London, where one of them being Apprehended, confestd the other, who upon his Tryal did acknowledge he was there, when the Robery was done, but that he came Accidentally, and did not meddle in taking any thing from the Prosecutor, there being three Fellows upon him, who had him down, &amp;c. of which the said Hawkson was one; but this Sham would not take, for upon the Evidences Swearing point blank, that he was one concern'd, they were both found <rs id="t16810706a-5-verdict19" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-verdict19" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"/>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16810706a-5-punish20" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-5-punish20" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"/>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-5-defend18 t16810706a-5-punish20"/>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-5-defend20 t16810706a-5-punish20"/>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
   
   
            <div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16810706a-6">
               <interp inst="t16810706a-6" type="collection" value="BAILEY"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-6" type="year" value="1681"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-6" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16810706A"/>
               <interp inst="t16810706a-6" type="date" value="16810706"/>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16810706a-6-off21-c17" targOrder="Y"
                     targets="t16810706a-6-defend25 t16810706a-6-off21 t16810706a-6-verdict23"/>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16810706a-6-defend25" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Plat
                  <interp inst="t16810706a-6-defend25" type="surname" value="Plat"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-defend25" type="given" value="John"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-defend25" type="gender" value="male"/>
                  </persName>
               
             took his Tryal, for <rs id="t16810706a-6-off21" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-off21" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-off21" type="offenceSubcategory" value="burglary"/>
               breaking open the House of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16810706a-6-victim27" type="victimName">
                           James 
                           Holms
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-6-victim27" type="surname" value="Holms"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-6-victim27" type="given" value="James"/>
                        <interp inst="t16810706a-6-victim27" type="gender" value="male"/>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y"
                              targets="t16810706a-6-off21 t16810706a-6-victim27"/>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , in the Parish of <placeName id="t16810706a-6-crimeloc22">Hornsey</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-crimeloc22" type="placeName" value="Hornsey"/>
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-crimeloc22" type="type" value="crimeLocation"/>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-6-off21 t16810706a-6-crimeloc22"/>, in the Company of several others (some of which have been already Executed) and taking thence Plate, wearing Apparel, coined Silver, and broad peices of Gold, to the value of 60 pounds, and Barbarously using the people of the House, by Wounding, Beating of them
            </rs>; he pleaded he was not there, but a great many Miles distant, at the time of the Robery, but not being able to produce Testimony thereof, and on the other side the Prosecutor Swearing positive, he was found <rs id="t16810706a-6-verdict23" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-verdict23" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"/>
               Guilty
            </rs> of the Fellony and Burglary.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16810706a-6-punish24" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16810706a-6-punish24" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"/>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y"
                           targets="t16810706a-6-defend25 t16810706a-6-punish24"/>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
   
   
